                *num += 1;

                condvar_clone.notify_all(); // Notify other threads
            }
        });

        handles.push(handle);
    }

    for handle in handles {
        handle.join().unwrap(); // Wait for all threads to finish
    }
}
```

### Summary

These implementations use mutexes and condition variables (or semaphores) to synchronize access to a shared resource (`count`) between two threads. Each thread waits for its turn based on the current count value, ensuring ordered output.

